About : 
=========
WhaTV is a simple information diffusion system, aimed to be used either in web
browsers or embedded in entreprise diffusion systems.


Changelog
=========

0.0.1 (2010-09-11)
----------------
Initial release.
[Cedric de Saint Martin]

0.0.2 (2010-09-11)
----------------
Iframe and video full support with proper css.
[Cedric de Saint Martin]

0.0.3 (2010-09-11)
----------------
Adding Flash support.
[Cedric de Saint Martin]

0.0.4 (2010-10-18)
----------------
Adding modular Ambimage support.
[Cedric de Saint Martin]

0.0.5 (2010-10-19)
----------------
Get rid of majority of jquery calls,
Ambilight support,
Adding an options system to specify image and video options (not fully implemented)
[Cedric de Saint Martin]

0.0.6 (2010-10-23)
----------------
Option system with (fullscreen, ambimage/ambilight, crop) options, every size calculated relatively for images and video,
Everything is vertically centered.

0.0.7 (2010-10-25)
----------------
Introducing a footer with a clock and a Quick Messages system.
[Cedric de Saint Martin]

Roadmap :
=========
09/26 0.0.7 : footer with date and Quick Messages
09/26 0.0.7.1 : beautiful CSS for footer, clock up?
09/29 0.0.8 : animated header
09/02 0.1.0 : First stable release with proper "finished loading" event firing, fix chromium video bug, no timeout for videos
10/05 0.2.0 : Widgets support
10/08 0.2.1 : Proof of concept : meteo widget
10/11 0.3.0 : Modular transition system with some examples
0.4.0 : Powerpoint support
1.0.x : Posting server, dynamic fetching of resources from server
1.1.x : Optional authentication system

Slide isolation : a failed slide won't prevent other to show correctly
Photo album module
Could it be possible to have x #content, where x is the number of slides?
CSS3 image animation support (examples : http://developer.apple.com/safaridemos/showcase/transitions/) 
Module system, where we specify urls of extensions files.